#: ../../tools.rst:4
msgid ""
"In order to provide a unified user experience and enable code reuse, the "
"editors for symbols, schematic, padstack, package and board are all based "
"on the interactive manipulator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tools.rst:9
msgid "How to select the right tool"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tools.rst:11
msgid ""
"To edit the things on screen, use the tools. Tools can be started in "
"multiple ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../tools.rst:14
msgid ""
"By typing in the tool's key sequence. Available key sequences are listed "
"by clicking the help button in the top right corner or typing :kbd:`?`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tools.rst:17
msgid ""
"By using the :doc:`Spacebar Menu<spacebar-menu>`. Just start typing for "
"the tool you're looking for or browse through the list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tools.rst:20
msgid ""
"By right clicking an object. This will bring up context menu listing all "
"the tools relevant to what's selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tools.rst:22
msgid "By pressing one of the dedicated buttons in the top bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../tools.rst:24
msgid ""
"After having started a tool, it receives all keyboard and mouse input, "
"till the tool is finished or you end it by pressing :kbd:`Esc`. Look at "
"the bar that appeared at the bottom of the canvas to see what pressing "
"keys will to in this particular tool."
msgstr ""

